The <strong>PREROUTING</strong> chain in iptables is used to process packets when they are received, that is,
before they are transferred to the corresponding network stack. This is the first place where you can find an incoming package on a Linux system.<br><br>
The chain operates at the core level, which means it can process packets very quickly and efficiently.
However, this also means that configuration errors can lead to serious problems with network connectivity.

